comments: Hart (POR) places his forearm to James' (LAL) side and marginal contact occurs contesting his driving shot attempt.
Nurkic (POR) establishes himself in Walker IV?s (LAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Davis (LAL) places his forearm to Lillard's (POR) side during his drive and delivers contact that affects his SQBR.
Davis (LAL) hands off the ball in Simons' (POR) path and momentarily places his hands to his upper body as he defends over the contact.
Lillard (POR) slightly lowers his hand during Beverley's (LAL) upward shooting motion and avoids making contact to his arm during his jump shot attempt.
Nurkic (POR) places a resting hand to Davis' (LAL) front and slides his hand off as he secures the loose ball.
Westbrook (LAL) places his hands against Simons' (POR) body in the lane and releases away as they pursue the loose ball.
Westbrook (LAL) defends over the pick and lightly brushes Lillard's (POR) arm during his drive.
Beverley (LAL) makes contact to Lillard's (POR) lower body during his drive and the contact affects his SQBR.
James (LAL) makes tactile contact to Lillard's (POR) shoulder as he loses his balance at the end of his drive.
Walker IV (LAL) cleanly dislodges Grant's (POR) driving shot attempt.
Grant (POR) legally contest James' (LAL) jump shot attempt.
Beverley (LAL) grabs Lillard's (POR) arm underneath the basket and the contact affects his ability to secure the loose ball.
Beverley (LAL) and Lillard (POR) mutually engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Nurkic (POR) is already established in Walker IV's (LAL) path and slightly extends as he rolls towards the basket.
Davis (LAL) moves along Simons' (POR) path, contesting his driving shot attempt and marginal contact occurs.
Beverley (LAL) momentarily places his arm against Lillard's (POR) extended elbow off ball and disengages.

Replay review of the foul called on Nurkic pursuant to a coach?s challenge was deemed successful. Nurkic (POR) establishes himself in Beverley's (LAL) path and slightly extends his forearm as he releases away from the contact. Beverely's reaction is not consistent with the level of contact.
Lillard (POR) does not get the ball across the mid-court line within 8 seconds. A 8 second violation should've been whistled.
Walker IV (LAL) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Lillard?s (POR) arm after the release.
Davis (LAL) and Winslow (POR) mutually engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Nurkic (POR) briefly places his hands against James' (LAL) body near the mid-court line and immediately removes them.
James (LAL) slides his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Beverley (LAL) retreats and makes incidental foot to foot contact with Winslow (POR) on the cut.
Toscano-Anderson (LAL) and Lillard (POR) come together and absorb each other's contact off ball.
Toscano-Anderson (LAL) grasps Lillard's (POR) arm as he defends over the screen and slides his hands off.
Grant (POR) maintains his arms within the frame of his body and does not deliver illegal contact to Toscano-Anderson (LAL) during the screen.
After hitting the ball, Davis (LAL) initiates incidental contact with Grant?s (POR) arm, contesting his driving shot attempt.
Beverley establishes himself in a screening position in Lillard's (POR) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Lillard (POR) places his hand against James' (LAL) body and absorbs the contact at the end of his drive.
Lillard (POR) legally contests James?s (LAL) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
